content.text:
- **Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor)** ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))  
  - URL: `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase`  
  - Direct quote snippets:  
    - “CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor / Cyclin-K glue-degrader.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))  
    - “under study ID: NCT06600789.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))  
    - “enrolling patients with advanced solid tumors, including ovarian, breast and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))  

- **Discovery of ZLC491 as a Potent, Selective, and Orally Bioavailable CDK12/13 PROTAC Degrader — PMC** ([pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11513923/))  
  - URL: `https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11513923/`  
  - Direct quote snippets:  
    - “Here, we report the discovery of ZLC491 as a potent, selective, and orally bioavailable CDK12/13 PROTAC degrader.” ([pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11513923/))  
    - “The compound effectively degraded CDK12 and CDK13 with DC_{50} values of 32 and 28 nM, respectively,” ([pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11513923/))  
    - “in TNBC MDA-MB-231 cells.” ([pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11513923/))  

- **Discovery and resistance mechanism of a selective CDK12 degrader — PubMed** ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33753926/))  
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33753926/`  
  - Direct quote snippets:  
    - “a CDK12-specific degrader, BSJ-4-116.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33753926/))  
    - “in combination with the poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase inhibitor olaparib” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33753926/))  

- **Degradation of CCNK/CDK12 is a druggable vulnerability of colorectal cancer — PubMed** ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34289372/))  
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34289372/`  
  - Direct quote snippets:  
    - “NCT02 is identified as a candidate with minimal risk of non-specific toxicity.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34289372/))  
    - “NCT02 acts as molecular glue that induces ubiquitination of cyclin K (CCNK)” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34289372/))  
    - “proteasomal degradation of CCNK and its complex partner CDK12.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34289372/))  

- **NCT 02 | Molecular Glues | Tocris Bioscience** ([tocris.com](https://www.tocris.com/products/nct-02_7551))  
  - URL: `https://www.tocris.com/products/nct-02_7551`  
  - Direct quote snippets:  
    - “NCT 02 acts as a molecular glue that induces proteasomal degradation of CCNK and CDK12” ([tocris.com](https://www.tocris.com/products/nct-02_7551))  
    - “CAS Number 790245-61-3” ([tocris.com](https://www.tocris.com/products/nct-02_7551))  
    - “Smiles  CC1=CN=C(S1)NC(CC2=COC3=C2C=C4CCCC4=C3)=O” ([tocris.com](https://www.tocris.com/products/nct-02_7551))  

- **Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor — PubMed** ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/`  
  - Direct quote snippets:  
    - “synthesized a potent PROTAC degrader PP-C8 based on the noncovalent dual inhibitors of CDK12/13” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  
    - “PP-C8 demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with PARP inhibitor in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC).” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  

- **Development of an orally bioavailable CDK12/13 degrader and induction of synthetic lethality with AKT pathway inhibition — PubMed** ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/))  
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/`  
  - Direct quote snippets:  
    - “a selective CDK12/13 PROTAC degrader, YJ9069,” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/))  
    - “an orally bioavailable CDK12/13 degrader, YJ1206,” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/))  
    - “in subsets of prostate cancer cells” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/))
